Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.96,0:01:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the big ones in the rear so they don't block traffic. Are we going this way? I guess we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.01,0:01:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow me. Okay. Hello, hello. We can do both sides at once
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.20,0:01:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe, yeah? We can do both sides at once, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning. Don't miss anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.20,0:02:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a hand or else pay a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.07,0:02:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.75,0:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Daniel Lyons. You remember the guy with the graph?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.21,0:02:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one is Daniel? Daniel Lyons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.93,0:02:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're showing his graph this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.99,0:02:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? I met you. Why didn't you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.55,0:02:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.90,0:02:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.90,0:02:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. Good morning. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.75,0:02:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.61,0:03:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.03,0:03:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I say hello to everybody? Did I miss anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.52,0:03:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God. Here's the whole roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.77,0:03:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.11,0:03:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.21,0:03:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.46,0:03:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.87,0:03:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.72,0:04:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.12,0:04:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's people my size.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.37,0:04:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We put the big ones in the back so they don't block the...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.70,0:04:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We put the big ones in the back and they don't block vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.97,0:04:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll go around the other side anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.49,0:04:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,John, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, Doc. Good morning, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.73,0:04:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Oh, he gets another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.08,0:04:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope you're around that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.12,0:04:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.31,0:05:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No fear to make me cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.42,0:05:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll save the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.43,0:05:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.27,0:05:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few announcements before we begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.10,0:05:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The typical cell phone's off, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the main entrance only, not the side doors all day, just in and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.92,0:05:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And please save your picture-taking, snapshots,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.74,0:05:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,until the Q&A, which is from 3 to 5, and no video-taking at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And real quickly, the schedule, the doctor's going to talk until 11.15,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.07,0:05:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we have our first 15-minute break.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.60,0:05:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's refreshments served in the universal room,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,which is straight out that way to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.83,0:05:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll be back here from 11.30 to 12.30.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.18,0:06:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is serious business.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.72,0:06:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.80,0:06:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.87,0:06:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.93,0:06:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.95,0:06:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.98,0:06:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.07,0:06:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.10,0:06:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.16,0:06:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.50,0:06:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Be back here at 2 until 2.45, and then we have our last 15-minute break,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.63,0:06:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bookstore closes at 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.19,0:06:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.16,0:06:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Amber Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.43,0:06:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to have you all here with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate you all showing your opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.56,0:06:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important in the word.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It means not only to me and myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.19,0:06:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing, we do have a cell phone right now with the 2002 series.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.56,0:06:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2002 is really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,basis of all the work, and so we have it in, only in VHS and audio tape, so this is on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:07:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sales, I think it's 25% off at this point, but it is the basis of the work, so if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in that, the bookstore has it, and we are going to have power versus force
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.02,0:07:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,on CPU, and that will be coming out, hopefully within about the next two to three weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.48,0:07:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so please check the website, so we've been working very hard on that for you, I know
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.30,0:07:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that's something that everybody's been waiting for, so, okay, and with that, I'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.69,0:07:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,present Dr. Dewey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.25,0:07:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,An Excelsior's deal, if anybody complains about something in one of the books, I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.38,0:07:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't you read the first page?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.68,0:08:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were forewarned, and I figure people who shouldn't read the book won't get past the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.55,0:08:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,first page, so I say, go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.93,0:08:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Excelsior's deal, Jesus, throw it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.81,0:08:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today we're talking about, we're talking about perception versus essence, perception
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.75,0:08:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,versus essence, yeah, perception versus essence, on the one hand, very simple, on the other
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,hand, very subtle, and difficult to describe, but we'll do it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem, the impossible just takes a little longer, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.42,0:08:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everyone have a fair idea of what that means, the difference between perception and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.95,0:08:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,essence?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.72,0:08:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody, who thinks it seems somewhat familiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.85,0:09:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.78,0:09:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here are new today, new?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh, all right, so, what we do is we sort of do a survey of all the, you know, the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.17,0:09:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,material that's been brought up before, in the beginning, and then we go on to the new
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.55,0:09:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,material, so there's something for the people who've been here before, and something new,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.77,0:09:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,something new for the people who've been here before, and a quick review, and a representation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.98,0:09:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The material is rather unique, because it came out of research, which had not been done
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.46,0:09:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It came about as a result of an observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.49,0:09:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Of a Course in Miracles class, came as a result of an observation of, I was doing kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.36,0:10:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,on people, and I needed somebody to demonstrate it that evening, and things that made everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak, like looking at fluorescent lights, or holding pesticides against your solar plexus,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.82,0:10:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,various things like that, all of a sudden, here was a few students on this Course in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.13,0:10:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles, and they did not know what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.79,0:10:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.24,0:10:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds and hundreds of people all went weak, and these people didn't go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.41,0:10:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that led to the realization that there had been a movement in consciousness, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.50,0:10:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we then discovered, by following new students in the Course, we would test them before they
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.53,0:10:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,took the Course, then we'd test them periodically, once a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.50,0:10:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And after about the third month, all the stimuli that make everybody go weak did not make them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.36,0:10:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.77,0:10:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had to do a little bit of a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.10,0:10:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had to do a little bit of a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had to do a little bit of a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had to do a little bit of a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.29,0:10:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had to do a little bit of a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.34,0:10:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We discovered a rather amazing discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:10:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's clinical science, not academic science.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Academic science, it doesn't even make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.70,0:11:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So we then discovered the whole scale of consciousness, and that launched all the research.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.24,0:11:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll start with slide one, and that's the one that's so familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to have started out of focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that in focus?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.33,0:11:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.23,0:11:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.28,0:11:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? Well, maybe it's those spotlights up there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.24,0:11:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if we can reduce the spotlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.34,0:11:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of fuzzed out. Isn't that fuzzed out?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.70,0:11:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.20,0:11:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be the spotlights, or maybe it's the focus on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.57,0:11:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Janice, is there a focus on the...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:11:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.55,0:11:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how things look as you get older, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.08,0:11:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That, to me, is normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.28,0:12:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a 1927 model here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.37,0:12:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We have more recent models on the road now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.35,0:12:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When I grew up, the Model T was the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.02,0:12:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Model T was the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then along came an amazing invention, the Model A.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.69,0:12:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.99,0:12:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's just to warn you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.55,0:12:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we don't need to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.10,0:12:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the spots could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.67,0:12:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's focus as well as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.65,0:12:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that as good as we can focus?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.41,0:12:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this sun that we normally have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.09,0:13:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, this sun, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.92,0:13:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought maybe it was these spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.46,0:13:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, anyway, everybody's familiar with the consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.55,0:13:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it follows the chain of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.05,0:13:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,On the left-hand side, what you really see is the levels here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.91,0:13:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,come from psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.39,0:13:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They come from the psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.60,0:13:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,These are emergency emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.84,0:13:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the great chain of being, Ken Wilber,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.72,0:13:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the perennial philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.67,0:13:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's repetitious throughout history,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that hatred is near the bottom and despair is near the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.87,0:13:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and that joy and happiness are up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The important thing is that God is up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At this end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.03,0:13:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not at the end of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.48,0:13:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people in the world seem to be at the end of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people in the world seem to be at the end of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.03,0:14:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people in the world seem to have this whole map turned around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.98,0:14:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Love and trust is weakness and to be despised,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.87,0:14:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and hate is masculine and good, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.39,0:14:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, the map of consciousness allows us now a way of discerning essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.25,0:14:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A way of discerning essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.74,0:14:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the map really does is give a calibrated level to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says, I come here out of friendship,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.48,0:14:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you calibrate him, he's 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.91,0:14:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.89,0:14:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Better search him, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.25,0:14:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He says one thing and he looks one way,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.96,0:14:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's up to something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.72,0:14:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.63,0:14:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So sometime it's subliminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.01,0:14:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Our intuition, we call it our intuition,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.58,0:14:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,picks up the essence, subliminal, body language,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.79,0:14:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,little subtle hints.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had to put your finger on it, you can't, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.00,0:14:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and women are supposedly better at this than men.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.66,0:14:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we think that's true?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:14:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's sexist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.45,0:15:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't say anything in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.44,0:15:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditionally, women were better at intuition than men.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.73,0:15:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say traditionally women were better at intuition in certain fields of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.27,0:15:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and men were intuitive in other fields of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.22,0:15:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In business, they can pick up, he's good for another grand easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.41,0:15:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think women are intuitive in their world,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.27,0:15:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and men we describe as intuitive in their world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.44,0:15:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, just...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.28,0:15:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I used to, you know, I was trained as a boxer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.14,0:15:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a mosquito weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.23,0:15:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I didn't weigh 90 pounds to make flyweight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.95,0:15:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we learned, to some degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.40,0:15:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you learn to intuit the other person's moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.95,0:16:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And never telegraph your punches.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.12,0:16:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand these interventions,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.44,0:16:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're international megalomaniac people
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.79,0:16:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that get up and telegraph their punches.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.55,0:16:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They tell the whole world what they're planning
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.50,0:16:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and where they've got it hidden and what they're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.60,0:16:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't have made mosquito weight, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.85,0:16:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Never telegraph your punches.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.69,0:16:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, with the right cross, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you're going to come with a left jab,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.66,0:16:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but you were really planning a right cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.50,0:16:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't let them know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.80,0:16:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't hold the right cross where you can see you're getting it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.40,0:16:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's dumb, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.37,0:16:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So dumb is the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the rule in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.12,0:16:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.63,0:16:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dumb between dumb and dumber.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.50,0:16:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Dumb and dumber.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.45,0:16:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dumb get up there and threaten everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.25,0:16:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dumber don't even complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:16:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't even get them to vote to complain
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.83,0:16:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,about this guy who's threatening to blow up the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.14,0:16:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's dumb and dumber.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.75,0:17:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a perception in essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're going to publish an atlas of all these slides eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.57,0:17:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're up to 89.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.90,0:17:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought 100 is a neat number,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.46,0:17:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so I got to manufacture 11 more out of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.84,0:17:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured by the end of the year, we'll have 100, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.82,0:17:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there will be an atlas with the slide,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.65,0:17:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and then at least a page of explanation, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.15,0:17:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get a quick run of what it's all about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.00,0:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,without having to read a lot of material.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.11,0:17:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So the scale of my calibrating,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.29,0:17:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness confirms spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirms spiritual realities, and that is a focus of interest,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:17:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Templeton group and people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.55,0:18:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you verify spiritual realities?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.85,0:18:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, people don't, you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.92,0:18:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's purely a subjective experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.43,0:18:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and until we had the calibrated levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.93,0:18:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no way to verify a spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.24,0:18:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, just the fact that everybody believes in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.55,0:18:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody believes in it, everybody believes in it, everybody believes in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.68,0:18:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you believe something, it doesn't make it a spiritual reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes it something that everybody believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.36,0:18:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual reality, then, has never been confirmable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.66,0:18:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's purely a subjective state, consequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It is outside the field of academic science.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way academic science can confirm spiritual reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.50,0:18:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because it would be transcending its own parameters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.72,0:18:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,its own paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.41,0:18:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty in confirming spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.82,0:18:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is the judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.67,0:18:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to move from one paradigm to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.89,0:18:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual dimension is a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.50,0:19:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't operate according to the Newtonian cause and effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.17,0:19:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,or mathematical models.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.45,0:19:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So perception has to do with projecting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.20,0:19:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,onto that which is really linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.72,0:19:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And essence, then, is non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.68,0:19:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You intuit the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.85,0:19:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and despite that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.09,0:19:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,despite your perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.71,0:19:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Enlightened states, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so as far as atheists,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.41,0:19:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they have a difficult time with all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.28,0:19:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they go past page one,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.80,0:19:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to run into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.65,0:19:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, God turns out to be infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates as infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.59,0:19:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I spent many years as a devout atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so I have sympathy for the atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.32,0:19:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have sympathy for genuine doubt,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.95,0:19:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's intellectual honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.10,0:20:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So it calibrates as honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.65,0:20:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If, honestly, I cannot say that I can confirm
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.69,0:20:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the believability of a divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.58,0:20:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at least being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.76,0:20:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And being honest is the first requirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.21,0:20:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So perhaps the best way to become enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.91,0:20:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is first being an honest atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.42,0:20:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Or at least a skeptic, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.09,0:20:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I move from atheist to,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.77,0:20:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the next one,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.33,0:20:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you can't say yes or no?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.44,0:20:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.53,0:20:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.61,0:20:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, first I was an atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.35,0:20:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,then I became more sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.50,0:20:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and became agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.79,0:20:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said it's not something that can be confirmed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,one way or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.89,0:20:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which made me a formal skeptic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.93,0:20:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a skeptic says you cannot arrive at truth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.60,0:20:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by reason or the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.82,0:20:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something that we reconfirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.93,0:20:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.67,0:20:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot arrive at truth by the mind itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.60,0:20:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the construction of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.89,0:21:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move on then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.55,0:21:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good enough start.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.15,0:21:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.78,0:21:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,here's the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.52,0:21:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority are less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.33,0:21:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to recalibrate the world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.40,0:21:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of humanity at this point
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.44,0:21:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is over 200, 204, 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.02,0:21:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,206, 207, 206.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.23,0:21:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.30,0:21:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,206.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.76,0:21:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was at 205 for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.21,0:21:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it went up briefly to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.93,0:21:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's 206.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.86,0:21:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,206, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.08,0:21:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the majority of the world then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.49,0:21:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.47,0:22:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That means non-integrity is the rule
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.52,0:22:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by which they live.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.26,0:22:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what America and our government doesn't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.08,0:22:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,80% of the world lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.56,0:22:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by completely different rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.01,0:22:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Being nice to them doesn't mean a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.98,0:22:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you're stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.96,0:22:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Any of you who've been in that part of the world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you haven't skewed the customer really good,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.86,0:22:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a failure and you get beaten when you get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.32,0:22:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You could have gotten so much for the carpet
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.30,0:22:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you only got so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.42,0:22:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the difficulty with the world today
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.25,0:22:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is the communication then
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.35,0:22:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two different levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.05,0:22:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is integrous here is ridiculous here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.83,0:22:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's re...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.52,0:22:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.24,0:22:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll move to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.29,0:22:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.64,0:22:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too depressing a subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.39,0:23:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, here are the people over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.21,0:23:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you see, because of their power,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.58,0:23:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they counterbalance all the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.78,0:23:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is a very, very significant factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.96,0:23:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,People in a group like this are counterbalancing,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.50,0:23:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.45,0:23:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,probably millions on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.28,0:23:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A group like this probably counterbalances
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.35,0:23:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of millions of people below people over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.66,0:23:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we move next up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.05,0:23:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Percent of elapsed time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.01,0:23:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel Lyon, who's here today, did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.72,0:23:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask, what do you think about the future of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.29,0:23:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when you calibrate the consciousness over time,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.44,0:23:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,percent of elapsed time,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.33,0:23:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that it's almost yesterday that it started
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.77,0:23:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to shoot up, and if this continues,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.81,0:23:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be quite rapid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.42,0:23:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So right now, we're at 205, 206, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.48,0:23:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.80,0:24:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think this is very interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.06,0:24:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from a religious-spiritual viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.00,0:24:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of consciousness throughout time on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.60,0:24:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At the age of the oldest rocks, we go back billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.25,0:24:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we see the emergence of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.36,0:24:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, it's the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.48,0:24:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of life on the planet moved ever so slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.22,0:24:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,millions and millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.29,0:24:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Three million years ago, Lucy appeared someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.90,0:24:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.70,0:24:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The first real human about three million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.96,0:24:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which is very recent, in Earth time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.61,0:24:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Three million years ago is like yesterday in Earth time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.16,0:24:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so we humans are very,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.85,0:24:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,newly emerged just hatched on this planet time-wise we're just hatched and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.42,0:25:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,barely got here okay then we'll move on next and we see the progression of the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.86,0:25:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of consciousness throughout the animal kingdom on up to Coco and our
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.47,0:25:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,kitty at home let's see our kitty at home let's do kitty our kitty our kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.00,0:25:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is over 200 220 250 260 270 280 to 75 kitties at 275 alright then kitties per
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.66,0:25:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let's do kitties fur kitties purrs over five hundred five ten kitties purrs at
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.53,0:25:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and that's the most amazing thing the heart of the kitty then
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.63,0:25:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.18,0:25:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the essence out of which he's coming, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.75,0:25:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.38,0:25:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the cat and the dog, just like some other animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.96,0:26:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,mainly cat and dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.13,0:26:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,radiate a certain energy that is quite different from any other animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.46,0:26:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog sees you coming and he just loves you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.50,0:26:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He just goes crazy over you, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.24,0:26:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a dog come up, he just goes out of his mind with happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.88,0:26:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot there we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.18,0:26:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And broccoli, let's see how broccoli is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.54,0:26:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli is our African gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.71,0:26:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli is over 300, 320, 340, 380, 400, 390, 395.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.76,0:26:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli is up to 390, coming right along.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.21,0:26:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She's speaking Spanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.08,0:26:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabe is teaching her Spanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.24,0:27:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in my study that the bird answers the phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.48,0:27:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rings the phone, answers the phone, and hangs up the phone and says goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.70,0:27:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes a buzzing sound like the phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.20,0:27:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then says, hello, hello, has this conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.59,0:27:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,says, I've got to go now, and then makes a click sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.88,0:27:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I go out in the other room, I think somebody's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.53,0:27:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.44,0:27:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye now, I've got to go now, click.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.49,0:27:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's, what did she calibrate? I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.43,0:27:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,380? What was it, 380?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.90,0:27:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've done her in class before.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.90,0:27:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we first got her, I forget what she was at, 285 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.90,0:27:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, she's moving along, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.50,0:27:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.22,0:27:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to reconfirm a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.91,0:27:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For those who are more intellectual, I think this is very interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.95,0:27:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the implications of this slide are profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.19,0:28:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the academic world really needs this information.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.51,0:28:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, these are the great minds throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.49,0:28:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see, they're all about the mid-400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.56,0:28:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Some get as high as 499, Freud, and who else?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.07,0:28:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.00,0:28:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Newton, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.46,0:28:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, 499, yeah, Plotinus is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.35,0:28:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But 499 is really the peak of what the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.74,0:28:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and reason are.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.79,0:28:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And what reason can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.74,0:28:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So it defines a paradigm, then, a region in which it's applicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.78,0:28:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not applicable elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.25,0:28:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not applicable once you get over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.15,0:28:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get over 500, you're talking about a different dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.91,0:28:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in which reason and logic and the linear constructs
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.63,0:29:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are no longer meaningful, appropriate, or applicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.36,0:29:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.02,0:29:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we cannot prove the existence of God by the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.85,0:29:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which is one of the reasons I was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.31,0:29:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I studied theology at a Jesuit university.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.53,0:29:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And classical theology, I said, that's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.51,0:29:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,First cause, the argument for first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.59,0:29:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.24,0:29:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,God's infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.92,0:29:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're infinite, you got no beginning and no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.68,0:29:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can there be a first cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.74,0:29:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.47,0:29:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So goodbye, theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.54,0:29:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I got an A in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.19,0:29:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I got an A in all those courses.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.21,0:29:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to be smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.47,0:29:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to know what you're arguing about.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.83,0:29:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something new in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.83,0:29:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The world I grew up in.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.09,0:29:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to know what you're complaining about.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.14,0:29:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we get emails, and when we do the arm on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.92,0:30:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, did this guy read the book?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.25,0:30:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I get no.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.47,0:30:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He's complaining he hasn't even read the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.95,0:30:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You open the page, you didn't like it, and send off an email.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.50,0:30:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like emails.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.06,0:30:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In the old days, you had to sit down,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.28,0:30:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and write a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.56,0:30:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out stationery, put a stamp on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.60,0:30:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,spend three cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.03,0:30:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.55,0:30:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They were three cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.40,0:30:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.11,0:30:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That took care of about 90% of the emails.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.27,0:30:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If they had to sit down and write a long-end letter
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.85,0:30:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and put three cents on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.29,0:30:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't be doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.29,0:30:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, not knowing anything about anything
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.29,0:30:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,does not stop them at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.35,0:30:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.70,0:30:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.55,0:30:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to move on fast today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.27,0:30:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this becomes applicable, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.94,0:30:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because here is perception focusing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.65,0:30:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is essence out here, is the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.44,0:31:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we talk about essence,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.03,0:31:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about a field,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.50,0:31:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which is often intuited, subliminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.50,0:31:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the more evolved consciousness gets,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.19,0:31:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you identify with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.41,0:31:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You have less and less identification with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.93,0:31:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and less than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.84,0:31:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and greater and greater identification,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.67,0:31:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with life itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.28,0:31:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with the essence of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.41,0:31:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You eventually end up identifying with consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.50,0:31:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.02,0:31:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the content of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.76,0:31:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because bodies come and go,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.47,0:31:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you think you're a body,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.56,0:31:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're going to die when your body topples over.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.82,0:31:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's good to realize you're something other than the body
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.80,0:31:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before it topples over.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.21,0:31:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Although you find out quick enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.60,0:31:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.73,0:31:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.20,0:32:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we talk about the field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.33,0:32:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.75,0:32:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The content, which is perception,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.74,0:32:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ego, it's linear, predictable, measurable, objective,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.00,0:32:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,deals with force, time, causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.60,0:32:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The proximate field has an influence on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.38,0:32:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but the infinite field,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.72,0:32:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the spirit out of which all knowingness arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.46,0:32:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the knowingness of that which is linear
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.31,0:32:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.06,0:32:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.39,0:32:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual foundation of virtues.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.24,0:32:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.48,0:32:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this was the world that I grew up in,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.16,0:32:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the 1927 model.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.16,0:32:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It went with the Model Ts and the Model As.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.20,0:32:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,These were all considered normality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.00,0:32:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.50,0:32:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the way your friends were,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.50,0:32:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,your friends were.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.77,0:33:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This was what life was.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.77,0:33:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we didn't know that anything else existed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.77,0:33:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,except John Dillinger, Machine Gun Kelly,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.77,0:33:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Babyface Nelson.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.64,0:33:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There was Mob Barker,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.18,0:33:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the criminal gangs,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.18,0:33:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there were these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.56,0:33:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And these people were all the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.56,0:33:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what's called traditional America.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.69,0:33:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.69,0:33:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you moved into a neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.69,0:33:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your neighbors came over and brought some tea to meet you,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.60,0:33:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody returned your lawn mower,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.60,0:33:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if you lend it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.47,0:33:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a sane, orderly world,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.47,0:33:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and people were friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.47,0:33:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There were some weird people,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.47,0:33:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but we just avoided them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.47,0:33:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.78,0:33:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The old crab that lived down in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.78,0:33:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk around her lawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.58,0:33:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.35,0:33:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But generally, everybody followed a certain model of normality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.44,0:34:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what was called normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.44,0:34:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing about the mind is that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.73,0:34:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it likes to dramatize everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.73,0:34:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is actually 99% silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.65,0:34:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is helpful when you're meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.00,0:34:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just helpful to know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.34,0:34:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,People become, they despair that they can't get their mind to stop
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.34,0:34:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.34,0:34:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It just goes right on talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.42,0:34:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's because they're looking at the content of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.42,0:34:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the mind itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.42,0:34:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind itself is that in which all this talkingness is going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.42,0:34:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind itself is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.42,0:34:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason you can hear a sound in the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.90,0:34:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the silence of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.90,0:34:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is 99% silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.57,0:34:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.92,0:34:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of your mind is doing nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.92,0:34:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.94,0:35:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the infinite field in which the story goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.94,0:35:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The story is only 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.94,0:35:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The story is only 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.96,0:35:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is for entertainment,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.96,0:35:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we become hypnotized by the 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.96,0:35:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We focus on the content of the 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.96,0:35:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And think that's the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.00,0:35:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.00,0:35:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what's going on in the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.00,0:35:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the action in the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.00,0:35:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.53,0:35:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.53,0:35:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To see something, it has to be an empty space.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.53,0:35:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To know what you're thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.76,0:35:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it would have to occur in a vacant field.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.96,0:35:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the sun shining right on this poor man's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.96,0:35:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.44,0:35:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we lend him a cap or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.51,0:35:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you want to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.51,0:35:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you blinded by the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.86,0:35:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks like he's blinded by the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.86,0:35:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we'll move on from this field.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.13,0:35:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The formula of causality then
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.13,0:36:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is that a oneness spreads out into its components
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.00,0:36:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and looks like causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.00,0:36:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.09,0:36:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.01,0:36:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as causality in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.01,0:36:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're dealing with reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.01,0:36:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,what you see is emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.25,0:36:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the understanding that creation and evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.51,0:36:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are one and the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.19,0:36:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is the secret to understanding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.44,0:36:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the infinite potentiality of the Godhead arises
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.61,0:36:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,God manifests as the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.30,0:36:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is eternally evolving and advancing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.30,0:36:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.30,0:37:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe is expanding at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.50,0:37:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.32,0:37:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Had to get a franchise on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.17,0:37:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What we think is causality
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.17,0:37:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is merely the way things emerge.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.17,0:37:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so if creation was constructed right from the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.17,0:37:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to be evolutionary in nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.17,0:37:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the preceding slides it's very obvious,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.17,0:37:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the intrinsic nature of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.55,0:37:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and physical reality is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.55,0:37:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is emerging.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.55,0:37:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is transforming and emerging.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.67,0:37:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.67,0:37:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we see is the sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.71,0:37:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The sequence is going on in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.71,0:37:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no sequence in the world anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.71,0:37:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,than there's causality in the mind, in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.28,0:37:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.28,0:38:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergence is a potentiality becoming an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.40,0:38:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when local conditions are favorable and facilitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.40,0:38:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The seed sits there until everything is just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.73,0:38:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun doesn't cause the seed to sprout.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.65,0:38:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The water doesn't cause it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.65,0:38:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who plants it there doesn't cause it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.98,0:38:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Its intrinsic nature is under certain
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.98,0:38:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the potentiality becomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.98,0:38:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.38,0:38:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody have any problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.38,0:38:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll explain it again if you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.67,0:38:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution and creation are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.78,0:38:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They were having a big argument about it in the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.78,0:38:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligent design and all the BS that goes on with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.78,0:38:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I sent a letter to the editor,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.05,0:38:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which I knew wouldn't get published,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.57,0:38:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it says, obviously,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.86,0:38:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution and creation are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.38,0:38:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But nobody wants to give up the argument, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.38,0:39:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all getting too much out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.30,0:39:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course they didn't publish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.36,0:39:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, lower mind, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.48,0:39:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at about 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.48,0:39:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the locus on the energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.86,0:39:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,like the chakra system,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.86,0:39:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,lower mind calibrates at about 155.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.86,0:39:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's concrete and literal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.26,0:39:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And higher mind calibrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.73,0:39:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what does it say, 275.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.73,0:39:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So perception, then, first has to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.73,0:39:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend lower mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.73,0:39:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which projects out there its own narcissistic needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.98,0:39:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Its own narcissistic needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.98,0:39:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the value of everything is based on
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.98,0:39:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,its narcissistic gratification.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.03,0:39:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you agree with that idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.03,0:39:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,if that idea agrees with you, you like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.03,0:39:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's narcissistically gratifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.03,0:39:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't agree with you, you hate it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.03,0:40:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's not narcissistically gratifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.03,0:40:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As you move up, you begin to accept
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.03,0:40:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that the end of reason may or may not
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.03,0:40:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,agree with how you view it,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.03,0:40:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're more mature and you accept
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.03,0:40:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that that's a likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.03,0:40:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here, it's not considered to be a likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.03,0:40:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just simply that you're wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.23,0:40:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and probably should be killed or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.23,0:40:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Burned at the stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.32,0:40:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The trouble with...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.78,0:40:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.30,0:40:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How about let's do you in the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.30,0:40:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated low in the United States right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.76,0:40:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 420.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.76,0:40:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,421.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.92,0:40:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,422.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.92,0:40:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,421.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.92,0:40:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's holding up pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.92,0:40:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding up pretty good despite the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.32,0:40:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because the media have sort of a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.32,0:40:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,naive, simplistic school child idea of fairness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.32,0:41:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that the alternate view should always have equal time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.15,0:41:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole program's about the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.78,0:41:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is round.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.78,0:41:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they're going to give equal time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.78,0:41:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to some idiot who lives somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.78,0:41:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in boo-boo land who thinks it's still flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.78,0:41:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The viewer's mind is naive, thinks that,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.26,0:41:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, this must be so.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.26,0:41:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is not true, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.48,0:41:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,gets equal exposure in the media
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.48,0:41:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with that which is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.48,0:41:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the downside of society,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.48,0:41:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which I think is its undoing eventually, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.61,0:41:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the undoing of society is by iteration,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.61,0:41:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,iteration meaning constant repetition
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.61,0:41:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of a small error.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.09,0:41:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,By iteration, you eventually destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.09,0:41:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a social structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.09,0:41:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the lie becomes equally okay with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.09,0:41:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And in many areas of the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.09,0:41:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that is already so.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.09,0:42:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The lie is equally valued as the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.44,0:42:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the downside of democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.44,0:42:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Most democracies only last two or three hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.44,0:42:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's because,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.65,0:42:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I call them the great unwashed ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.46,0:42:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what I used to call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.46,0:42:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You call them the great unwashed,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.46,0:42:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,have an equal vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.46,0:42:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So if they have equal time,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.78,0:42:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,fair and balanced,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.78,0:42:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that's fair and balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.78,0:42:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So falsehood has equal time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.78,0:42:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and equal emphasis,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.78,0:42:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's equally glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.78,0:42:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's even more glamorized
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.78,0:42:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's more dramatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.78,0:42:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The crazy professor gets more time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.78,0:42:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,than the sane person.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.98,0:42:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the lore of mind then.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.98,0:42:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.98,0:42:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.98,0:42:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all familiar with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.98,0:42:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the world of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.01,0:42:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And quantum mechanics, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.01,0:42:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way out from the linear domain
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.01,0:42:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.01,0:42:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,via the Heisenberg principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.01,0:43:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we have the interesting discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.01,0:43:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that to observe a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.01,0:43:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is already to change the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.01,0:43:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already changed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.01,0:43:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You've introduced something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.01,0:43:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You've introduced the impact
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.01,0:43:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.01,0:43:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.80,0:43:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't know anything about
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.80,0:43:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.80,0:43:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So my intuition is that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.80,0:43:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.80,0:43:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of the observer
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.86,0:43:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,has a profound effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.86,0:43:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only does observing it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.86,0:43:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,change the outcome,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.86,0:43:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,collapse the wave function,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.86,0:43:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality to anaxiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.86,0:43:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but the power of observation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.86,0:43:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of the observer
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.86,0:43:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can have a very profound effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.19,0:43:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And such things, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.19,0:43:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can result in fallacious
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.19,0:43:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,research.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.15,0:43:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The Templeton Foundation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.34,0:43:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,spent one million dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.34,0:43:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to study the efficacy of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.34,0:43:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.61,0:43:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The recent study
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.61,0:43:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that got a lot of publicity out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.61,0:44:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the Journal of Cardiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.61,0:44:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 190, 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.61,0:44:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.61,0:44:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,One million dollars,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.80,0:44:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,five or ten years' worth of research,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.80,0:44:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,published in Cardiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.80,0:44:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit all the newspapers
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.90,0:44:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the last couple of weeks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.90,0:44:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.90,0:44:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer doesn't work for healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.90,0:44:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The research calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.82,0:44:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.88,0:44:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Fallacious,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.88,0:44:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.88,0:44:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacious by design.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.88,0:44:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Crick's experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.65,0:44:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that led to the discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.65,0:44:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of the DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.65,0:44:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.65,0:44:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,His last experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.38,0:44:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,before he left the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.38,0:44:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he left the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.48,0:44:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at a good time, I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.05,0:44:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated at 170.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.11,0:44:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That was to prove
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.11,0:44:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.11,0:44:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing but
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.11,0:44:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the product of neuronal activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.11,0:44:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, mechanistic reductionism
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.11,0:44:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is so important
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.11,0:44:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and so primitive
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.11,0:44:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and stupid
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.11,0:44:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't think anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.11,0:45:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with a good IQ
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.11,0:45:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,could fall for it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.11,0:45:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.11,0:45:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a big argument in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.11,0:45:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligent design,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.11,0:45:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,components and all such.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.32,0:45:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see what the opposition is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.32,0:45:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to intelligent design.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.32,0:45:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't say
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.32,0:45:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God's intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.32,0:45:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it just says intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.32,0:45:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a little bug
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.32,0:45:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,has intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.73,0:45:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How niggardly can you be
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.73,0:45:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.73,0:45:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,allow intelligence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.73,0:45:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to play any part?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.73,0:45:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The little bug goes like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.73,0:45:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he goes like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.73,0:45:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now he gets that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.73,0:45:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,this is where you eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.73,0:45:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that intelligence?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.03,0:45:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.03,0:45:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.13,0:45:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear gradations,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.23,0:45:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.23,0:45:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no long end
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.48,0:45:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the yardstick
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.48,0:45:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because from where
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.48,0:45:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're observing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.48,0:45:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,now this is the long side,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.48,0:45:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,now this is the short side.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.48,0:45:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if I move from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.48,0:45:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the long side
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.48,0:45:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the short side.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.48,0:45:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.48,0:45:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,what you see out there
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.48,0:45:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is a function of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.48,0:45:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the point of observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.48,0:46:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The point of observation
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.80,0:46:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,determines what you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.80,0:46:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we'll move on,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.90,0:46:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.90,0:46:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual practices,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.21,0:46:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this is verifying
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.15,0:46:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual realities,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.15,0:46:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,verifying spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.15,0:46:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that we presume
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.28,0:46:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to be so,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.28,0:46:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but this is like
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.28,0:46:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,confirmatory,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.28,0:46:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,confirmatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.28,0:46:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord's Prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.28,0:46:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,650, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.28,0:46:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Om pronounced
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.32,0:46:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,om, not om
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.32,0:46:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or a-u-m,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.32,0:46:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the incorrect
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.44,0:46:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pronunciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.44,0:46:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Om namah shivaya,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.61,0:46:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,shanti shanti,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.61,0:46:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,om mana padme hum.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.69,0:46:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll resume later.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.51,0:46:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.51,0:46:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Gregorian chants.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.51,0:46:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I love Gregorian chants.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.84,0:46:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I said I wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.84,0:46:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a diverger
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.84,0:47:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in a great cathedral
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.84,0:47:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you sit there
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.84,0:47:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you hear the choir
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.84,0:47:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,practicing all day Saturday,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.84,0:47:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Gregorian chants.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.84,0:47:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.21,0:47:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.21,0:47:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, I was a boy soprano.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.21,0:47:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy soprano.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.21,0:47:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.53,0:47:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a wonderful life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.98,0:47:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice Wednesday night,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.98,0:47:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,practice all day Saturday,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.98,0:47:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and then practice Sunday morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.98,0:47:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you get a bowl like that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.98,0:47:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kata, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.40,0:47:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.40,0:47:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the religious upbringing,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.46,0:47:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which has a favorable effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.46,0:47:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.46,0:47:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,on neuronal connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.46,0:47:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thing you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.46,0:47:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for a child
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.46,0:47:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is classical music,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.67,0:47:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual or religious upbringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.67,0:47:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you had playing chess,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.94,0:47:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd get an extra note,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.94,0:47:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one more point.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.42,0:47:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sing the rosary,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.42,0:48:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,pilgrimage to Mecca,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.86,0:48:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,12 steps of AA.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.09,0:48:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,12 steps are very powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.09,0:48:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.09,0:48:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.21,0:48:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that's reached by 0.4%
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.21,0:48:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.21,0:48:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.21,0:48:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.21,0:48:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,570 is saintliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.75,0:48:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Current Pope, the last Pope was 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.13,0:48:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This Pope's about the same, 567 or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.96,0:48:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's perfect for the head of a world church.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.15,0:48:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get beyond 570, the whole thing becomes idiotic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.84,0:48:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and you want to deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.36,0:48:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you keep saying, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.28,0:48:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as he's used to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.26,0:48:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.73,0:48:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And TM, prayer of Jebez, walking in the labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.09,0:48:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We do that here in Sedona at St. Andrews, St. Andrews, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.63,0:49:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Genuflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.51,0:49:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, all these things here at 540 are all acts of devotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.53,0:49:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,acts of devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.00,0:49:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I always get spoiled when I go to Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.17,0:49:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because in Korea, everyone greets each other
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.23,0:49:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in what I consider the only civilized manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.84,0:49:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They meet each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.80,0:49:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you're walking through,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.96,0:49:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the clerks and everybody, complete strangers,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.98,0:49:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,greet each other with a certain reverence,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.44,0:49:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which I find very, very meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.61,0:49:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer of St. Francis of Assisi,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.92,0:49:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,bathing in the Ganges at the Wailing Wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.65,0:49:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,devotional burning, turning prayer reels,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.21,0:49:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,devotional acts, hand clasps.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.71,0:49:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.38,0:49:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All these are really contributory.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.23,0:49:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we say how ignorant, turning a prayer reel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.00,0:49:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.57,0:49:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.28,0:49:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.55,0:50:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intention is the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.32,0:50:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention is the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.03,0:50:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the field that elevates it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.84,0:50:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.15,0:50:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Progressive fields of realization, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.07,0:50:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are from form, which registers a recognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.40,0:50:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.50,0:50:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because part of consciousness is the watcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.98,0:50:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer, which comes out of awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.03,0:50:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer-witness, the light of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.96,0:50:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So in meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.11,0:50:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in meditation and in evolution as your consciousness progresses,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.88,0:50:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you identify farther and farther back into this field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.09,0:50:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to know and to it that you are this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.82,0:50:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty easy to get to the watcher, experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.05,0:50:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty easy to grasp that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.96,0:50:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll move to the observer-witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.92,0:50:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can let go identifying with that and without much effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.78,0:50:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,move back and realize that it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.40,0:50:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize observing and witnessing is a phenomenon of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.90,0:51:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't decide to observe or witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.67,0:51:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Your say-so, you don't have no say-so whether you're going to observe or witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.42,0:51:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You open your eyes, you're observing and witnessing already.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.42,0:51:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an automatic phenomenon of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.67,0:51:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's easy to let go of a personal eye here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.32,0:51:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to be a genius to realize the observer,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.51,0:51:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,observing, witnessing is an automatic phenomenon of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.21,0:51:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.73,0:51:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to know that, because of the light of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.23,0:51:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, with a little contemplation,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.53,0:51:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can move and realize that what is of significance,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.44,0:51:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the core of your reality, is the light of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.92,0:51:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.96,0:51:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I going to take a break? What time?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.63,0:51:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I drink. I give up drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.88,0:52:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I spit it all on booze and women and the rest are wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.09,0:52:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.15,0:52:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And where we grew up in traditional America was sort of piety, piety.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.63,0:52:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Long robes, monks' cowls, crucifixes, saying the rosary,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.94,0:52:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,giving up meat for Fridays, giving it up for Lent.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.13,0:52:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It was penance and piety and confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.38,0:52:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality has to do with joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.88,0:52:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy has to do with laughter, seeing the humor of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.38,0:53:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't see the humor of life, it's going to be hard to get through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.13,0:53:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You chop off your thumb, you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.11,0:53:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what the hell, I didn't need it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.30,0:53:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's this one I use.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.00,0:53:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor Susie.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.88,0:53:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, she said she was going to tie me down today, but I got loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.00,0:54:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.19,0:54:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual evolution has to do with joy, joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.76,0:54:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Piety has its place, but beyond piety is joy, and beyond joy is ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.76,0:54:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an overwhelming ecstasy with enormous energy, enormous non-stop energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.13,0:54:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can dance 24 hours a day without ever stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.13,0:54:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All physiologic functions stop, and you're in a very exalted, ecstatic state.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.98,0:54:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't know how you get out of it, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.55,0:54:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it comes to you that that, too, has to be surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.05,0:54:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what came in that state of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.34,0:54:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This, too, had to be surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.67,0:54:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the ecstasy was surrendered, then a great peace, peace beyond all description,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.11,0:55:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace of God descends.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.30,0:55:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So beyond joy is ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.07,0:55:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And beyond ecstasy is an infinite peace, sat-chit-ananda, non-linear, with no content.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.44,0:55:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the core of one's existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.44,0:55:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It is bliss and forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.48,0:55:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, you can leave the body, 50% too.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.48,0:55:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember, the door is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.48,0:55:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to continue on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.00,0:55:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.00,0:55:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, there was a surrender to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.55,0:55:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine will of whether the body would continue on or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.59,0:55:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.59,0:55:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets up and walks around, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.59,0:55:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't get up and walk around, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.59,0:55:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's equal, of no significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.59,0:55:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's God's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.73,0:56:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.76,0:56:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's God's problem, it's not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.76,0:56:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.51,0:56:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the spiritual energy, then, comes up as the kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.05,0:56:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as your consciousness evolves, the kundalini energy rises,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.55,0:56:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and creates certain phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.55,0:56:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the first phenomena it creates is,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.96,0:56:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the outflowing of this kundalini energy then,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.96,0:56:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs, starts to flow at level 200, and advances very strongly.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.71,0:56:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates the etheric brain, creates the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.21,0:56:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And it modifies the physical brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.71,0:56:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as the kundalini energy rises,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.71,0:56:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then, you experience things differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.71,0:56:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with a different side, a different dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.71,0:56:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The right brain is now dominant, instead of the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.71,0:56:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 80% of the world, or whatever it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.76,0:56:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of the world, live here out of the animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.76,0:57:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Greed, hatred, anger, narcissistic self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.76,0:57:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Exploitation of others, there's nothing wrong with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.76,0:57:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's business, they call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.09,0:57:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here, it starts to bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.59,0:57:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here is where it bothers you,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.09,0:57:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when you walk by the little black beetle,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.09,0:57:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I always use him as an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.09,0:57:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here, you see a black beetle, you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.73,0:57:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,give him another swoosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.92,0:57:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, you see the black beetle, but you're busy,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.25,0:57:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you walk by, now it grabs you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.80,0:57:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, heck.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.67,0:57:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You go over and you turn him over.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.17,0:57:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you walk, you're happier, you're happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.34,0:57:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Little beetle walks away, he's happy too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.84,0:57:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Life serving life, out of love of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.63,0:57:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all life becomes equally valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.63,0:58:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So his little dilemma, you know, grabs you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.63,0:58:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Under 200, his dilemma doesn't, you call the exterminator.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.63,0:58:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.40,0:58:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that the level of consciousness determines the rate of happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.42,0:58:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of poverty, criminality,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.55,0:58:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the happiness rate, the rate of criminality,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.55,0:58:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is directly aligned with the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.05,0:58:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Directly at the consequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.09,0:58:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not due to some environmental out there in this,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.09,0:58:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.09,0:58:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way you come out of it is by taking responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.50,0:58:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I agree with that comedian who gets people annoyed
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.42,0:58:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by pointing out that you're the people that created the crime here,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.42,0:58:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the people that created the poverty here.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.42,0:58:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Crosby.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.42,0:58:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Crosby, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.42,0:58:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Crosby, you know, is trying to get them to come out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.42,0:58:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Take responsibility for your own actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.92,0:58:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,stop blaming it on others.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.92,0:59:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see what happens to the rate of employment,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.05,0:59:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.55,0:59:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.25,0:59:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of criminality drops way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.75,0:59:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Down at the bottom, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.25,0:59:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a lifestyle of a whole society.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.75,0:59:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole society lives here, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.25,0:59:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.50,0:59:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness as related to international affairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.05,0:59:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of great significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.55,0:59:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we know, I call this us and them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.96,0:59:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is us, and this is them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.09,0:59:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, us can be our company, it can be our community,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.40,0:59:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be our family, it can be our,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.46,0:59:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in this case, it's our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.46,0:59:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we calibrate the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.46,0:59:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of who we're dealing with diplomatically,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.46,0:59:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see that you've got to change your languaging,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.46,1:00:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to change what carrots you hold out to,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.65,1:00:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,something that's a carrot here is meaningless down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.71,1:00:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The carrot works up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.98,1:00:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Same carrot doesn't work down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.98,1:00:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't eat carrots.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.98,1:00:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We hang the same carrot in front of everybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.03,1:00:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of the rabbit and in front of the lion.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.19,1:00:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lions don't like carrots, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.96,1:00:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lions down here, at calibrated level 90 or something,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.98,1:00:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,don't like carrots.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.19,1:00:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that simple?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.15,1:00:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And meat doesn't appeal to these people here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.13,1:00:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.13,1:00:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To be effective and successful,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.13,1:00:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to change our languaging based on our awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.13,1:00:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the consciousness level,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.13,1:00:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the field in which these people live.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.13,1:01:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we're just talking into a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.13,1:01:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And we spend most of our time talking into a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.82,1:01:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What time have we gone?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.69,1:01:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we've got 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.19,1:01:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.92,1:01:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I want to see where we are
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.92,1:01:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because I want to save a good deal of time for what's new.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.26,1:01:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay, wonderful, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.26,1:01:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we have three new slides.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.26,1:01:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, we've got 89 slides altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.55,1:01:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've got three new ones for today.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.55,1:01:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we wanted to do first for the people that are new
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.55,1:01:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a quick review and add a few comments as we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.63,1:01:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This I consider to be of profound importance
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.13,1:01:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in world affairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.13,1:01:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only possible way to pace, as far as I can see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.26,1:01:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the science of international diplomacy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.26,1:01:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,based on calibrating the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.26,1:02:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the leader, the people, and the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.26,1:02:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to know all three.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.88,1:02:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have great people,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.38,1:02:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but they've been taken over by a terrible ruler.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.88,1:02:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have wonderful people and a good ruler,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.01,1:02:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but the government, the economy is rotten through and through.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.53,1:02:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's payola wherever you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.76,1:02:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Payola wherever you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.80,1:02:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole economy and the government,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.80,1:02:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so life doesn't get better there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.80,1:02:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are wonderful people, we love them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.80,1:02:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the president is a wonderful guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.80,1:02:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But the structure in between doesn't work, it's horrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.82,1:02:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get all kinds of admixtures of the three.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.82,1:02:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you'd have a really realistic expectation
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.36,1:02:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of what you can deal with.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.36,1:02:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If we calibrate the level of a visiting ruler,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.61,1:02:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we know how to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.61,1:02:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We know what they value, what's meaningful,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.61,1:02:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the field of reality in which they live.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.96,1:03:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the field of reality in which they live?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.01,1:03:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting a free alligator would not tempt me
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.78,1:03:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to get into a deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.78,1:03:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, doc, you do as you get a free alligator,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.78,1:03:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it would not attract me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.28,1:03:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So we offer free alligators to a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.53,1:03:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who are not interested in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.53,1:03:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we say, how come we can't make a deal with them?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.69,1:03:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't get a deal on, what, Iran right now, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.19,1:03:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't even get people to agree
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.69,1:03:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that they don't like the idea
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.69,1:03:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of being blown up by an atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.69,1:03:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't even agree they don't like that idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.73,1:03:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot get the governments of the world to agree
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.73,1:03:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's not a great idea and they should say so.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.01,1:03:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe that?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.71,1:03:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get the governments to agree
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.71,1:03:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that blowing people up with atomic bombs is not a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.09,1:03:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you can't take the world seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.09,1:04:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.23,1:04:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.01,1:04:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we just see the level of evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.01,1:04:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.01,1:04:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Percent of people who are happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.01,1:04:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see a huge jump at level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.90,1:04:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Below level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.40,1:04:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,people find gratification and fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.40,1:04:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take that, you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.59,1:04:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Dillinger and Babyface Nelson felt good
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.59,1:04:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as they pumped them full of lead and grabbed the money and ran.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.59,1:04:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not the same thing as happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.07,1:04:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's instant gratification.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.32,1:04:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Plunging the dagger into somebody you hate,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.82,1:04:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it feels good.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.32,1:04:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Take that, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.92,1:04:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, that feels good. I should have done that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.25,1:04:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Snicker snack.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.00,1:04:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Which lifetime am I in right now?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.51,1:04:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, where are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.51,1:04:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a different lifetime, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.51,1:04:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We put each other away.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.01,1:05:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we ever put each other away?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.01,1:05:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We put each other away.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.84,1:05:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it for Jesus, he did it for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.13,1:05:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We both left the body at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.13,1:05:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And both broke out laughing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.90,1:05:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We were good, we were good.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.21,1:05:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the best.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.71,1:05:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I put it right through him and he put it right through me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.21,1:05:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The bodies fell over and we both went out in the spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.21,1:05:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and just laughed. It's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.92,1:05:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it for Jesus, he did it for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.05,1:05:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we never had to repeat that one again.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.65,1:05:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We've helped each other periodically over a great deal of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.65,1:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.05,1:05:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How to identify spiritual truth and integrity as teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.05,1:05:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have another lecture later in the year
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.84,1:05:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we cover most of this again.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.11,1:05:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm thinking of constructing a new religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.61,1:06:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We need a whopper of a good name for it, let's recall.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.73,1:06:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth whether you like it or not, religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.28,1:06:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth for nickel biters.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.13,1:06:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nickel biters, how do you know it's true, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.25,1:06:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so is this, no, we've got to go back one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.25,1:06:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, identification of spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.92,1:06:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's so much that is not spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.92,1:06:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of what's in the spiritual bookstore is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.42,1:06:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.44,1:06:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Some bookstores that are just all in the way, just 90% BS.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.48,1:06:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But the average spiritual bookstores are about 50%, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.53,1:07:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything from the Da Vinci Code to, what's the newest one?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.53,1:07:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jesus thing. No, Judas, Judas Gospel.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.53,1:07:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Judas Gospel.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.71,1:07:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can discern essence, what would we guess the essence of that is, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.46,1:07:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to guess 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.13,1:07:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.63,1:07:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 130, 140, 150, 150, 155.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.86,1:07:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Gospel according to the Jews is about 155.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.51,1:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's total BS, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.01,1:07:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you write a fiction in the year, you wrote a fiction thousands of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.78,1:07:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not truer because it's on an old piece of papyrus.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.78,1:07:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was BS then and it's BS now.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.75,1:08:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Da Vinci Code is BS when it was written and it's BS now, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.34,1:08:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can make a movie out of it, I'm going to make it true, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.05,1:08:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.94,1:08:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary, what was it, Jesus and Mary got married and had kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.94,1:08:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I mean, the whole thing goes boom, boom, boom.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.93,1:08:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes a great story.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.28,1:08:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason there's so many books going to come out like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.28,1:08:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a whole bunch of them about to come out,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.28,1:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is because it made millions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.28,1:08:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can see the spiritual intention there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.05,1:08:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's warp history.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.35,1:08:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's throw in some big names like Jesus, Mary,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.35,1:08:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12 apostles, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.35,1:08:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Put some big names in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.35,1:08:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Beats, who's the guy, the Scientologist that had a kid?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.65,1:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom Cruise, right. Beats Tom Cruise, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.01,1:08:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.27,1:09:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so universally, truth is true at all times and all places.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.43,1:09:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact that it's on television and has, you know, music in the background.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.98,1:09:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The other way that falsity enters the media is music.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.02,1:09:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't understand what's being said on the program because of the music.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.27,1:09:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the History Channel.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.27,1:09:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the history of the British Crown, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.27,1:09:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the music drums up like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.27,1:09:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the music drowns out.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.27,1:09:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to get what Edward III said about the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.77,1:09:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy on the music thing thinks that it's all about music.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.27,1:09:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,People getting killed and dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.07,1:09:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People being beheaded.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.57,1:09:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Crowns are falling.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.07,1:09:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe is changing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.57,1:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And this guy is, I can see him in his circuit board here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.57,1:09:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know those big boards they have on a rock band?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.07,1:09:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's like, the music is rising up and rising up.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.07,1:09:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And just then, and just then,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.57,1:10:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and just then, what for Christ's sake?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.97,1:10:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I write the History Channel all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.47,1:10:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you stop drowning out the story?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.38,1:10:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a guy that gives the history of Britain,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.38,1:10:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an incredibly smart guy, I forget his name,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.38,1:10:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shalm or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.94,1:10:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And just when he gets to a critical point, you want to know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.44,1:10:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the music swells on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.05,1:10:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is always true.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.05,1:10:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's available to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.27,1:10:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Its purpose is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.27,1:10:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody owns it. Nobody sells it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.52,1:10:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No requirements.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.52,1:10:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-controlling.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.39,1:10:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Free of force and intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.39,1:10:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.38,1:10:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.27,1:10:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.80,1:10:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What number slide are we at now, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.80,1:10:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-two.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.80,1:10:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-two.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.97,1:10:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.64,1:11:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get to heaven without a program grad, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.14,1:11:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They ask you right at the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.68,1:11:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How many slides did you get through?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.56,1:11:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-two?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.13,1:11:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Under forty-two.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.84,1:11:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to go back to earth and go from forty-two through to eighty-nine.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.71,1:11:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so truth is beyond opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.30,1:11:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception has to do with rejecting an opinion, an evaluation, a judgment.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.30,1:11:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.89,1:11:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth does not do anything, it just is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.31,1:11:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth doesn't try to promote itself, it just stands there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.73,1:11:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is power does so out of the quality of its essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.90,1:12:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It transforms things
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.90,1:12:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequent of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.57,1:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that which it says, not that which it does.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.02,1:12:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which it does and says
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.02,1:12:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is merely an expression of its essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.02,1:12:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When you experience the joy of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.22,1:12:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy of life is joyful.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.22,1:12:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.26,1:12:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it. Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.42,1:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to sit on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.65,1:12:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, Susie comes and says,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.14,1:12:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll just stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.30,1:12:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-operative, does not do anything, it just is.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.57,1:12:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's invitational, so it grows by attraction rather than promotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.10,1:13:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also characteristic of the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.67,1:13:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not promotional, they don't have any opinions on what's out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.67,1:13:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and they grow by attraction, by attraction of their integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.93,1:13:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-sentimental.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.05,1:13:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.65,1:13:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-egoistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.18,1:13:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Educational.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.68,1:13:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-supporting.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.18,1:13:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Free-standing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.42,1:13:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.92,1:13:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go back and finish a little of these up again after the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.92,1:13:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then I'll finish it up now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.60,1:13:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go back to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.52,1:13:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we can't go back to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.52,1:13:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take a break now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.02,1:13:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take a break now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.02,1:13:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't want any laughing during intermissions.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.43,1:13:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I want piety.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.85,1:14:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody to be really spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.34,1:14:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't started yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.97,1:14:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't start until I say we start.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.94,1:14:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual teachers are not controlling.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.22,1:14:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start when I say we start.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.32,1:14:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody else can leave the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.60,1:14:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's up to a group vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.69,1:15:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All in favor of our starting, say aye.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.89,1:15:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, group vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.89,1:15:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the confirmation of spiritual realities is really the, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.84,1:15:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a great benefit of calibrating levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.23,1:15:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to tell because perception precludes awareness of essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.22,1:15:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to discern essence doesn't really arise.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.22,1:15:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Classically, it's called the opening of the third eye of the Buddhic body.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.77,1:15:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the etheric bodies, the etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.68,1:15:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.68,1:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the third eye of the Buddhic body opens.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.10,1:15:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it starts to open around 200, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.10,1:15:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it starts to open.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.10,1:16:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The third eye of the Buddhic body begins to open at level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.10,1:16:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.68,1:16:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it starts opening at 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.65,1:16:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and then its capacity grows over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.67,1:16:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So eventually, you know, you can tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.67,1:16:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you hear,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.15,1:16:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute we heard the Gospel of Judas and this old papyrus,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.15,1:16:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're all going about the reality of this old papyrus,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.65,1:16:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got nothing to do with, I don't give a crap
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.15,1:16:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what this million years old piece of papyrus,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.15,1:16:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what's written on there, that's what I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.50,1:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you instantly get that you're being hyped, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.50,1:16:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to up the viewership, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.50,1:16:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they can increase their advertising rates, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.00,1:16:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with truth, it has to do with hype.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.14,1:16:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get the difference between hype and truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.14,1:17:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth doesn't need hype, it stands on its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.40,1:17:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth stands on its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.43,1:17:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it may not be recognizable as truth
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.50,1:17:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,until consciousness does evolve to certain levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.25,1:17:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've relied over time, am I blocking somebody's view?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.65,1:17:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't want you, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.85,1:17:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.73,1:17:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We've relied then on people who have evolved more spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.73,1:17:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and we understand from their writings and their teachings.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.85,1:17:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that in itself causes confusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.60,1:17:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see there's disparity between
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.60,1:17:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the literal teachings of the various teachers,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.72,1:17:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the naive person gets confused.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.72,1:17:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps to clarify what is being explained by the teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.64,1:18:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if you know the calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.85,1:18:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So this person here is not telling you the ultimate truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.85,1:18:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he's telling you what truth looks like at consciousness level 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.85,1:18:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He's telling you what consciousness level 575 looks like.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.17,1:18:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Confucius, of course, Socrates, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.30,1:18:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're telling you what the world looks like,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.11,1:18:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what reality looks like from that particular level.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.11,1:18:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I was a starting student,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.56,1:18:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I would start from the lowest levels and first
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.56,1:18:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,become familiar with the lower, you know, the teachings.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.68,1:18:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Be kind to black beetles on their back.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.47,1:18:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.39,1:18:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Read Chinese fortune cookies and take them seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.39,1:19:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We told you that fortune, Chinese fortune cookies
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.05,1:19:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate around 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.97,1:19:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a Chinese fortune cookie is far beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.97,1:19:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.02,1:19:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.06,1:19:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind is at 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.97,1:19:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinese fortune cookies are at 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.71,1:19:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Gail and Robert brought us Chinese food the other night.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.71,1:19:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The fortune cookie calibrated over 300, 350, 360, 380.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.39,1:19:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,375.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.89,1:19:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The fortune cookie calibrates at 375.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.85,1:19:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it'll say something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.85,1:19:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The wise man knows how far to go and when to stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.85,1:19:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.85,1:19:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And other people, the fool, lunges ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.85,1:19:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,First, make sure you've got fortune cookies mastered.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.00,1:20:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Move on from fortune cookies.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.64,1:20:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When the fortune cookie life describes what your life is like,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.64,1:20:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you are making good progress.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.64,1:20:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You are way ahead of most of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.14,1:20:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Be kind to your neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.26,1:20:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Be thoughtful of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.26,1:20:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.76,1:20:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this is kindness and wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.26,1:20:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what it teaches is wisdom and, I think, wonderful sayings.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.76,1:20:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how fortune cookies got to be so fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.11,1:20:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to come back in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.11,1:20:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll come back as a Chinese fortune cookie.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.61,1:20:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a good start.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.61,1:20:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off from 350, you've got a running start.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.27,1:20:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what most people want to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.27,1:21:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you what a 90 person does.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.27,1:21:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They look for the highest number here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.27,1:21:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly, they scan this.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.27,1:21:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They find 950.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.27,1:21:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll start there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.81,1:21:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Starts with, you don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.31,1:21:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.93,1:21:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.93,1:21:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where I started out at age three.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.13,1:21:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.13,1:21:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For a three year old, that was a conundrum, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.68,1:21:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.23,1:21:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the oblivion of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.23,1:21:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because my prior spiritual commitments had been to the pathway of negation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.32,1:21:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time I'd leave the body, I'd go into nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.84,1:21:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, nothingness is not the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.97,1:21:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you could stay there.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.89,1:22:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing about nothingness is that it's painless.
