Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.02,1:36:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is extremely impressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.56,1:37:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is enlightenment. It matches everything you've ever heard, read, and it usually comes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.39,1:37:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of a long stretch of spiritual endeavor. And suddenly, there's nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.17,1:37:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No you, no person, no nothing linear, and it's eternal. And it's infinite peace and
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.06,1:37:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite calm and infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.81,1:37:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that's wrong with it is it's devoid of the warmth of the power of the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.35,1:37:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of God as infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.52,1:37:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's infinite love.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.11,1:37:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In this lifetime, that had come out at age, I don't know, 14 or something, in which I
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.47,1:37:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,climbed out, as I've said before, out of a storm into a snowbank. And there, the infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.23,1:38:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,bliss, the infinite presence, as infinite love.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.52,1:38:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So in that infinite Void at 850, that's what was missing, was that I already experienced
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.06,1:38:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the incredible bliss.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.02,1:38:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The incredible state, the condition of love, which is beyond all beginning and all endings.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.61,1:38:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not different than that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.52,1:38:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are is not different than that love.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.47,1:38:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So that knowingness was already there, and therefore, I refused the Void this time, and
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.57,1:38:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't get stuck there.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.07,1:38:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, that's how I'd go about starting over.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.97,1:38:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd start right at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.06,1:38:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this takes you five or ten years.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.06,1:38:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure how long it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.06,1:38:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.06,1:38:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe ten years.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.06,1:38:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it takes you twenty years.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.06,1:38:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.06,1:38:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.06,1:38:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's so delightful, the whole trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.06,1:38:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, it's very fascinating reading, and you become transformed just by exposure
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.56,1:38:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to the material.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.56,1:39:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's enough about all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.50,1:39:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What holds the level of consciousness is the dualities of attraction and aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.06,1:39:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That level of consciousness has a certain attraction to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.82,1:39:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.82,1:39:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also an associated aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.39,1:39:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is just general attractions and aversions that keep people fixated at any particular
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.10,1:39:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.97,1:39:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They get a thrill out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.27,1:39:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They get a kick.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.27,1:39:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They get a payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.81,1:39:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So what holds anybody at any particular level of consciousness is that level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.11,1:39:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,has payoffs in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.64,1:39:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're unwilling to give up is the payoffs.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.56,1:39:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The feeling of vindictiveness when you're right and they're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.55,1:39:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what's more fun than being right and having other people wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.00,1:39:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hard one to beat, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.00,1:40:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even chocolate is hard to...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.00,1:40:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you rather have chocolate and let go of chocolate or being right?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.30,1:40:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hard one, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.02,1:40:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we get addicted.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.11,1:40:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody at any level of consciousness means you're already addicted to the payoffs.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.11,1:40:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Addicted to the payoff of a certain positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.96,1:40:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to let go of the positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.42,1:40:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to let go of the addiction to the juice, the payoff of that positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.80,1:40:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to give up being right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.39,1:40:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be right all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.39,1:40:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.52,1:40:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, who cares?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.52,1:40:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, who cares?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.23,1:40:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the narcissistic gratification.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.42,1:40:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.61,1:40:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these dualities then...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.22,1:40:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yield a narcissistic gratification, look how people cling to being the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.85,1:41:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The gender card, the race card, the poverty card.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.44,1:41:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, they play it to death, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.97,1:41:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The tragedy card.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.19,1:41:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lost a member of my family.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.64,1:41:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lost every member of my family.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.52,1:41:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's going to lose all the members of your family.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.76,1:41:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us are staying here, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.89,1:41:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's going to lose everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.89,1:41:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.89,1:41:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the time, eventually. Does that get you a 20-minute spot on TV? Lately it does. I have
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.35,1:41:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to just blubber and cry and make a big calamity out of it. That's really juicing it, isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.06,1:41:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it? Juicing it. So you can see the narcissistic ego of these people getting up there juicing
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.88,1:41:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it. I mean, it's nauseating. They just juice it and juice it. Night after night, the same
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.44,1:41:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,people juicing the same story. They lost one person in their family. Christ, I've lost
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.44,1:42:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,half a dozen already. I mean, so what's a dozen? Probably a dozen. All right. The attraction
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.94,1:42:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then is you cling to it because you get juice out of it. And the aversion is to let go of
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.72,1:42:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the juice. The aversion is letting go of the juice. The attraction is the payoff. And the
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.48,1:42:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,aversion is to letting it go. It's much more fun to blame people than to let them go. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.18,1:42:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Blame.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.61,1:42:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Blame.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.80,1:42:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Blame.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.18,1:42:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as there's...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.73,1:42:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as there's a sad story on television, the very next person, the next talking head
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.61,1:42:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes out, and we're looking for who to blame. Katrina. Who should we blame for
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.14,1:42:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Katrina? How about the weather?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.63,1:42:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.47,1:42:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,George Bush. Poor old George. Everything. Everything's George. Katrina's George. The
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.46,1:42:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,war's George. The weather's George. Economy's George. The price of gasoline is George. Poor
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.97,1:42:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,old George.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.23,1:43:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But we need George to beat up on. So, he serves the function.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.80,1:43:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever's president gets beat up by. It used to be Clinton, you know. Whoever's president,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.69,1:43:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you beat up on him. That's why you can't get people of a certain caliber to be president.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.19,1:43:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's his name, the former actor, was...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.46,1:43:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.85,1:43:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.61,1:43:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.38,1:43:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.84,1:43:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.69,1:43:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.43,1:43:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan was over 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.52,1:43:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.35,1:43:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's very unusual. Very unusual. Usually by 500 you know what the score is.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.69,1:43:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to beat you up to death, spit on you, and who needs it, and pay you a lousy 200 grand a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.69,1:43:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the President used to get paid, 200,000. I thought it was outrageous.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.65,1:43:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can run a pizza parlor and make 200,000, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.97,1:43:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The President of the United States gets paid 200,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.97,1:44:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he gets 400, yeah. He's a what?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.52,1:44:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The President of some corporation just got paid off, what, 400 million to exit. 400 million to exit.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.52,1:44:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The President of the United States gets 400,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.52,1:44:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the attraction then, we cling to it because it's familiar, it's got a guaranteed payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.52,1:44:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next slide. Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.89,1:44:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is love versus infatuation. People are not interested in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.50,1:44:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Infatuation, of course, is what's sold as love.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.90,1:44:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, it's really a madness, it's a mental illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.00,1:44:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Passionate attraction, it calibrates 145.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.00,1:44:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the mating animal in heat. The mating animal in heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.76,1:44:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see it on the nature, nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.78,1:45:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All the animals humping away.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.26,1:45:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's stuff that if I...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.26,1:45:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, they would tear the page out of the book in the library.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.60,1:45:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Elephants doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.60,1:45:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Menasres is doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.60,1:45:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to know about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.89,1:45:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,145. So it's instinctual, it's left brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.02,1:45:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hormonal, as everybody knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.25,1:45:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And it drives you to murder and suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.25,1:45:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than that, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.10,1:45:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.10,1:45:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's passion, 145.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.10,1:45:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.10,1:45:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is something else, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.10,1:45:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So love at 500 and over has to do with concern for the other person's happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.10,1:45:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't need something from the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.10,1:46:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.10,1:46:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You appreciate it, you appreciate it, you value it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.10,1:46:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not a cravingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.10,1:46:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the dualities of shame, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.84,1:46:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the attraction...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.84,1:46:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We sing self-punitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.84,1:46:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that awful?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.84,1:46:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But no, that's what is sought.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.84,1:46:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's sought is to punish yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.31,1:46:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The child makes a mistake, now you've got to go sit in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.31,1:46:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the child gets...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.31,1:46:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Be bad, get punished.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.31,1:46:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Be bad, get punished.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.31,1:46:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way you get absolution is by punishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.31,1:46:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-flagellation and all the things...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.38,1:46:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sing the rosary, all the various things that religion does with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.47,1:46:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction is...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.77,1:46:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.77,1:46:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So the duality is the shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.77,1:46:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the book, the most recent one, what is the name of that one?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.85,1:46:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, Transcending Levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.69,1:46:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We go into each level, then, and examine each level.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.69,1:46:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What holds you there?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.69,1:46:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What's its attraction?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.69,1:46:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do people get stuck in it?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.69,1:47:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do you have to let go of to get off it?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.69,1:47:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you have to let go of to see is that really a sacrifice or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.07,1:47:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on out of shame and more shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.69,1:47:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, I'm ashamed of this chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.03,1:47:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.56,1:47:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame, you like beating on yourself instead of blaming it on the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.59,1:47:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't think you should do spiritual work without holding Socrates' dictum in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.59,1:47:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that all men choose only the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.88,1:47:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That gets you out of hatred and blame and self-condemnation
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.88,1:47:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because the human mind is so constructed that it craves that which...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.88,1:47:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Its cravingness is based on perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.88,1:47:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A projected value.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.88,1:47:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And all men choose only the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.88,1:47:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What Socrates says is you can't choose anything else
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.90,1:48:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,except what you conceive of as being the good at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.90,1:48:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be killing somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.03,1:48:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He deserves it, so the good is to stab him to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.03,1:48:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The good might be blowing up infidels.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.44,1:48:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very popular nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.60,1:48:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Straps and bombs on yourself and blow up a busload of infidels.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.60,1:48:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cool, you know, in certain cultures.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.52,1:48:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.52,1:48:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So because the person conceives that that is the way to please God,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.14,1:48:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore Jesus Christ said,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.14,1:48:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive them and they know now what they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.14,1:48:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of trying to follow religious dictum,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.39,1:48:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which is hard to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.39,1:48:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving those SOBs who don't deserve it,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.39,1:48:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,just as Jesus said it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.39,1:48:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's okay for Jesus to say that.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.68,1:48:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn't have somebody parking in his place.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.68,1:48:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.68,1:48:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,.
